  "body": "### Describe the bug\n\nSee https://github.com/keycloak/keycloak/issues/26799 - Keycloak users are effectively setting the quarkus.http.root-path to a value that does not end in a slash (as documented), then when accessing that path see an IndexOutOfBoundsException\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nThe filter logic should succeed.\n\n### Actual behavior\n\nContainerRequestContext.getUriInfo().getMatchedURIs() results in an IndexOutOfBoundsException\n\n### How to Reproduce?\n\n- Set quarkus.http.root-path=/foo\r\n- Install a filter that accesses getMatchedURIs():\r\n```\r\n    @Override\r\n    public void filter(ContainerRequestContext requestContext, ContainerResponseContext responseContext)\r\n            throws IOException {\r\n        System.out.println(requestContext.getUriInfo().getMatchedURIs());\r\n        return\r\n    }\r\n```\r\n- Access /foo in the browser\n\n### Output of `uname -a` or `ver`\n\n_No response_\n\n### Output of `java -version`\n\n_No response_\n\n### Quarkus version or git rev\n\nat least versions 3.2 - 3.7\n\n### Build tool (ie. output of `mvnw --version` or `gradlew --version`)\n\n_No response_\n\n### Additional information\n\nThe logic in ResteasyReactiveRequestContext.getPathWithoutPrefix is allowed to resturn an empty string when stripping the prefix, but logic like ResteasyReactiveRequestContext.saveUriMatchState assumes that the path is at least a single character - presumably /.",
